Lance Corporal Joshua Leakey rescued a wounded US Marine in Helmand in August 2013 . 
  He showed 'complete disregard' for his own safety during the firefight . 
  He is the sixth living British soldier to be awarded the Victoria Cross . 
  The Queen told him: 'I don't get to give this one out very often' He is second member of his family to receive the honour after a cousin was given it 70 years ago . 
  He braved heavy Taliban fire to rescue the wounded Marine . 
 